The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         BRIEFS
                  
	Behrampore, July 15: A man hacked his wife to death in a Murshidabad village after be- ing denied Rs 20 to clear his dues in a liquor shop.    
	With blood dripping and a scythe stuck on her shoulder, Tuntuni Bibi, 35, ran out of her house at Khagraghat, 210km from Calcutta, last night, calling neighbours for help. She slumped to the ground before the shocked villagers could react. Police said her husband Abdul Khalek, 45, is missing. His stepmom has been arrested.        
	Calcutta: A bill to prevent panchayat heads and their deputies from being re-elected within a year of being removed by a no-confidence motion was passed on Tuesday. It also makes it mandatory for panchayat samitis to hold at least one meeting a month.        
	Behrampore: The BSF has seized 240 tor- toises from Murshidabad. They were being smuggled to Bangladesh.                                                                                                                                                                   
